cs.HC, cs.GR, cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.IR

Reasoning: 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on how people read and interpret graphs, and uses eye tracking as a method to study this. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper deals with graph layout and visualization. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are less likely but still possible categories as the paper uses image analysis techniques (eye tracking) to study how people read graphs. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is also a possible category as the paper deals with how to improve the readability of graphs, which is relevant to information retrieval tasks.
